description:
This is a 21 minute workout called 'Conquer Your Fears Row' from the channel Aisyah Rafaee.
The workout falls under Cardio/Indoor rowing.
It's suitable for Intermediate fitness levels.
You'll need Rower for this workout.
The workout has a The Endorphin Wave and The Meditative Grind vibe.
The The Endorphin Wave vibe means Elevated energy, feel-good movement, steady build. This is especially good for When you want a challenging but steady burn. The The Meditative Grind vibe means Zone in, lock down, let repetition take over. This is especially good for Those who love a slow burn and rhythmic intensity..
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Moderate.

Original workout description: Description: Push through your limits on the Charles River with Aisyah as you tackle a rhythm climb paired with shorter intervals. This 20-minute sweat session is all about making decisions and facing fears, just like in a big race. Starting with a five-minute interval at rhythm 20, you’ll climb in intensity while the intervals get shorter—culminating in a heart-pounding one-minute sprint at rhythm 28. As you navigate each challenge with strength and determination, get ready to discover what you’re made of. Max rhythm: 28. Format: Climb...
